{
    "level": "sentence",
    "abstract": [
        {
            "text": "Results based on 106 M \u03c8 \u2032 events and about 226 M J/\u03c8 events acquired with the BESIII detector at BEPCII are reported, including a confirmation of the BESII pp threshold enhancement in J/\u03c8 \u2192 \u03b3pp, branching ratios for \u03c7cJ \u2192 \u03c0 0 \u03c0 0 and \u03b7\u03b7, and first measurements of the branching ratios for \u03c8 \u2032 \u2192 \u03c0 0 hc and hc \u2192 \u03b3\u03b7c, as well as measurements of the mass and width of the hc. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 0,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Also reported are first observations of the two photon process \u03c8 \u2032 \u2192 \u03b3\u03b3J/\u03c8 and f0(980) \u2212 a0(980) mixing.",
            "paragraph_rank": 0,
            "section_rank": 1
        }
    ],
    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The Beijing Electron-Positron Collider has been upgraded to a two-ring collider (BEPCII) with a design luminosity of 1 \u00d7 10 33 cm \u22122 s \u22121 at a center-of-mass energy of 3.78 GeV. ",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "It will operate between 2 and 4.6 GeV, allowing precision studies of charmonium (J/\u03c8, \u03c8 \u2032 , \u03c8(3770), \u03b7 c , \u03c7 cJ , and h c ), charm (D and D s mesons), and improved determinations of the tau mass and the hadronic cross section (R) in this energy region. ",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Details on BESIII and BEPCII are described in Ref. ",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "[1].",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 3,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "During 2009, BESIII acquired a sample of 106 M \u03c8 \u2032 events, or four times the CLEOc sample, and about 226 M J/\u03c8 events, or about four times the BESII J/\u03c8 sample. ",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "Results in this paper are based on these data sets.",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "II. ",
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "hc STUDIES",
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "In 2005, CLEO [2] reported a measurement of the mass of the h c ( 1 P 1 ) in e + e \u2212 \u2192 \u03c8 \u2032 \u2192 \u03c0 0 h c , h c \u2192 \u03b3\u03b7 c , where they used both inclusive and exclusive \u03b7 c decay events. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 14,
                    "end": 17,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "[2]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "In 2008, they repeated their analysis with 25 M \u03c8 \u2032 events. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "[3] Combining results, they obtain m(h c ) AV G = 3525.2 \u00b1 0.18 \u00b1 0.12 MeV/c 2 . ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 3,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "[3]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 71,
                    "end": 74,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w0"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "[3] A precise determination of the mass is important to learn about the hyperfine (spin-spin) interaction of P wave states. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 3,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "[3]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Using the spin weighted centroid of the 3 P J states, < m( 3 P J ) >, to represent m( 3 P J ), they obtain \u2206m hf (1P ) = < m( 3 P J ) > \u2212m( 1 P 1 ) = +0.08\u00b10.18\u00b10.12 MeV/c 2 . ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 166,
                    "end": 169,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "This is consistent with the lowest order expectation of zero.",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "BESIII has measured m(h c ) from the distribution of mass recoiling against \u03c0 0 s, both in inclusive \u03c8 \u2032 \u2192 \u03c0 0 h c samples and with samples tagged by the E1 photon from h c \u2192 \u03b3\u03b7 c . ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "This allows for the first time determinations of B(\u03c8 \u2032 \u2192 \u03c0 0 h c ) and B(h c \u2192 \u03b3\u03b7 c ). ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "BESIII also measures for the first time the width \u0393(h c ). ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Results are shown in Table I and compared with CLEOc and theory. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 21,
