        {
            "text": "54.3 \u00b1 6.7 \u00b1 5.2 41 (NRQCD) [5] 88 (PQCD) [ Because of the large \u03c8 \u2032 sample and the large branching fractions for \u03c8 \u2032 \u2192 \u03b3\u03c7 cJ , BESIII is in a good position to study both inclusive and exclusive \u03c7 cJ decays. Since \u03c7 cJ decays to two gluons, these decays are a good place to search for gluonium. [7] The color octet mechanism is important in these decays, [8] and measurements allow tests of theoretical models.",
