        },
        {
            "text": "BESIII observes \u03c7 cJ \u2192 \u03b3\u03c6 for the first time. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "BESIII has also fit the helicity angle distributions in the decays \u03c7 c1 \u2192 \u03b3V . ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The helicity angle is the angle between the V direction in the \u03c7 c1 rest frame and a daughter meson in the vector meson rest frame (\u03c1 or \u03c6) or the normal to the decay plane in the \u03c9 rest frame. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Longitudinal (transverse) polarization exhibits a cos 2 \u03b8 (sin 2 \u03b8) dependence. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Results for f t , where",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "N t is the number of fitted transversely polarized events, N l is the number of fitted longitudinally polarized events, and R is the ratio of the efficiencies for transversely and longitudinally polarized events, are given in   Two photon transitions are well known in excitations of molecules, atomic hydrogen, and positronium but except for the discrete transitions \u03c8 \u2032 \u2192 \u03b3\u03c7 cJ , \u03c7 cJ \u2192 \u03b3J/\u03c8 have never been observed in charmonium systems. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "BESIII has searched for continuous two photon transitions using \u03c8 \u2032 \u2192 \u03b3\u03b3J/\u03c8, J/\u03c8 \u2192 l + l \u2212 events, where l is e or \u00b5. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Selection requirements are used to reduce backgrounds from \u03c8 \u2032 \u2192 \u03b3\u03c7 cJ , \u03c7 cJ \u2192 \u03b3J/\u03c8 and \u03c8 \u2032 \u2192 \u03c0 0 J/\u03c8 and \u03b7J/\u03c8. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The invariant mass distributions of the two leptons for selected events are shown in Fig. 2. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 85,
                    "end": 91,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Fig. 2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "A clear excess is seen at the J/\u03c8 peak over \u03c8 \u2032 background from Monte Carlo simulation plus continuum background. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Branching fractions of B(\u03c8 \u2032 \u2192 \u03b3\u03b3J/\u03c8) of (1.06 \u00b1 0.08) \u00d7 10 \u22123 and (0.99 \u00b1 0.07) \u00d7 10 \u22123 are determined for the J/\u03c8 \u2192 ee and J/\u03c8 \u2192 \u00b5\u00b5 cases, respectively. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Combining, we determine B(\u03c8 \u2032 \u2192 \u03b3\u03b3J/\u03c8) = (1.02 \u00b1 0.05 +0.19 \u22120.20 ) \u00d7 10 \u22123 . ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 54,
                    "end": 59,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "text": "+0.19"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "This is a first measurement. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The result is preliminary, and more details can be found in Ref. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The f 0 (980) and a 0 (980) are controversial particles. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "They have been described as qq or qqqq states, KK molecules, or qqG hybrid states. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Mixing was first suggested by Achasov, [16] and mixing measurements may be important to clarify the nature of these particles. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 39,
                    "end": 43,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b13",
                    "text": "[16]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "There have been suggestions [17] for BESIII to search for mixing signals in J/\u03c8 \u2192 \u03c6f 0 \u2192 \u03c6a 0 \u2192 \u03c6\u03b7\u03c0 0 , where the f 0 mixes to a 0 , and in the process [18] \u03c7 c1 \u2192 \u03c0 0 a 0 \u2192 \u03c0 0 f 0 \u2192 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 \u03c0 0 , where a 0 mixes to f 0 . ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 28,
                    "end": 32,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b14",
                    "text": "[17]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 152,
                    "end": 156,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b16",
                    "text": "[18]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The signal for the former case is shown in Fig. 3 a). ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 43,
                    "end": 52,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_2",
                    "text": "Fig. 3 a)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The expected mixing signal is very narrow (8 MeV/ 2 ) between the K + K \u2212 and K 0 S K 0 S thresholds (987 -995 MeV/ 2 ). ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 45,
                    "end": 48,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w2"
                },
