                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Backgrounds are sideband and a wide a 0 from J/\u03c8 \u2192 \u03b3 * /K * K \u2192 \u03c6a 0 . ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Fitting to signal plus backgrounds determines 24.7 \u00b1 8.6 mixing events or < 36.7 at the 90% confidence level (C.L.). ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "This gives a mixing intensity \u03be f a = (0.6 \u00b1 0.2 \u00b1 0.2)% or < 1.1% at the 90% C.L. For the latter mixing case, we determine \u03be af = (0.32 \u00b1 0.16 \u00b1 0.12)% or < 0.91% at the 90% C.L. Figure 3 b) shows our results and upper limits compared to models (qq, q 2q2 , KK, and qqg) and calculated values (SND, KLOE, BNL, and CB) based on f 0 and a 0 parameters. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 180,
                    "end": 191,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_2",
                    "text": "Figure 3 b)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "References for models and calculations may be found in Refs. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "[17] and [18]. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3,
