        },
        {
            "text": "Ours are the first direct measurements. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "BESII observed a pp threshold enhancement in J/\u03c8 \u2192 \u03b3pp. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "[19] Fitted to a S-wave resonance, it gives a mass below pp threshold of M (pp) = 1859 +3+5 \u221210\u221225 MeV/c 2 . ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 4,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b17",
                    "text": "[19]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 99,
                    "end": 102,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w4"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "BESIII has confirmed this observation [20] in \u03c8 \u2032 \u2192 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 J/\u03c8, J/\u03c8 \u2192 \u03b3pp with a fitted mass of M (pp) = 1861 +6+7 \u221213\u221226 MeV/c 2 and directly in J/\u03c8 \u2192 \u03b3pp with a fitted mass of M (pp) = 1859\u00b10.8 (preliminary and statistical error only), shown in Fig. 4 a). ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 38,
                    "end": 42,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b18",
