                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 123,
                    "end": 126,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w5"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "CLEOc also observes a pp threshold enhancement in \u03c8 \u2032 \u2192 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 J/\u03c8, J/\u03c8 \u2192 \u03b3pp and obtains a consistent fitted mass. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "[21] BESII also observed a resonance at M (\u03b7 \u2032 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 ) = 1833.7\u00b16.1\u00b12.7 MeV/c 2 in J/\u03c8 \u2192 \u03b3\u03b7 \u2032 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 where \u03b7 \u2032 \u2192 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 \u03b7 and \u03b3\u03c1. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 4,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b19",
                    "text": "[21]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 74,
                    "end": 77,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w6"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "[22] BESIII also confirms this observation with a mass of M (\u03b7 \u2032 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 ) = 1842.4\u00b12.8 (preliminary and statistical error only), as shown in Fig. 4 b). ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 4,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b20",
                    "text": "[22]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 142,
                    "end": 151,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_3",
                    "text": "Fig. 4 b)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Many results, many preliminary, have been presented based on BESIII samples of 106 M \u03c8 \u2032 and about 226 J/\u03c8 events. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Many more results are to be expected in the future. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "In addition, BESIII acquired nearly 1f b \u22121 of data at the \u03c8(3770) resonance this year, including approximately 75pb \u22121 of scan data around the \u03c8(3770) peak. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Decays of the \u03c8(3770) produce quantum correlated DD pairs, which are ideal for mixing and CP violation studies, as well measurements of absolute branching fractions and studies of semi-leptonic decays. ",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "This sample allows BESIII to begin their charm physics program.",
            "section": "II. hc STUDIES",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3,
